post_text:
The State is no longer reimbursing for bus miles for meal delivery so buses will no longer run during the month of July. There will be no meals provided this week.

Starting on July 6th, we will continue to provide meals (breakfast and lunch) distributed to any child ages 1 through 18. Meals will only be available for pick-up in Grangeville at Grangeville Elementary and the Family Dollar parking lot and Clearwater Valley Elementary from 11:00 AM until 12:00 P.M. Monday through Friday through July 31st.

The Clearwater Valley High School's GRADUATING CLASS OF 2020 is invited to the Kooskia City park on May 22, 2020 at 7pm to enjoy pizza and watch their graduation ceremony on a big screen together! Please bring your own chair! Due to the Covid 19 we are unable to have the annual Safe and Sober night but we still wanted to do something special for the kids!
Questions please contact Melissa Carter or Tina Roy via Facebook messenger. Thank you all for helping make this day special for our graduating seniors! ♡
Sincerely,
CV class of 2020 Senior Parents

post_text:
Effective 03-25-2020

Busses will run on previously established routes morning and afternoon Monday through Friday from now until at least April 7th. 2020.

Children ages 1 to 18 years of age are eligible to receive a breakfast and a lunch bag combo free of charge. Eligible children can choose to get their meal bags in the morning or afternoon bus route.

Eligible children may receive a breakfast and a lunch bag combo by coming to a bus stop location once per day and a distribution center in the mornings only.

In addition to bus stops, distribution locations and times are:

7:30-8:30 Clearwater Valley Elementary
7:30-8:30 Grangeville Elementary-Middle School
7:30-8:30 Family Dollar parking lot
